 supply us with a word for every occasion—and this linguistic “wunderkammer” is here to prove precisely that. So whatever date this book has found its way into your hands, there’s an entire year’s worth of linguistic curiosities waiting to be found.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aEnglish languagexEtymology. 7aREFERENCE / General.2bisacsh  aEnglish language etymology, birthday holiday gift fun language, English language definitions fun, intelligent English puns, word of the day, eternal calendar, British European history, language, almanac, linguistics, yearbook, annual, English, word origins, definitions, words, odd words, English language, etymology, phrase, loanword, anecdote, obscure, logophile, Haggard Hawks, historical figures, dates, birthday, holiday gift, pun, wordplay, defintion, meaning, acceptation, quibble, semantics, paronomasia, crank, amphibology, old English words fun.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071194340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226646848423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226646848/original  a978-3-11-071194-3  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles